<section class="brand--ministry-of-defence brand__border-color organisation__brand-border-top organisation__section-wrap organisation__margin-bottom" id="what-we-do">
  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--padding gem-c-heading--margin-bottom-2  ">What the Advisory Committee on Conscientious Objectors does</h2>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-row">
    <div class="column-two-thirds">
      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak " data-module="govspeak">
    
          <p></p>
<div class="govspeak">
<p>We advise the Secretary of State for Defence on all conscientious objection claims. These claims are made by those in the armed forces whose application for permission to retire, resign or be discharged have been refused by the service authorities.</p>

<p><abbr title="Advisory Committee on Conscientious Objectors">ACCO</abbr> is an advisory non-departmental public body, sponsored by the <a class="brand__color" href="/government/organisations/ministry-of-defence">Ministry of Defence</a>.</p>
</div>

          <p>
            <a href="/government/organisations/advisory-committee-on-conscientious-objectors/about" class="brand__color">
              Read more about what we do
            </a>
          </p>

</div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>



